"By looking at the list of fields that are being compared you can say \042We are splitting by...\042 and then name a field.  For instance, Delta wants to split by SystemOfRecord (SOR).  By comparing them we can roll the lines up in to one when they are the same, but preserve the separate rows when they are different.  If they are different we'll have two lines with two date ranges when we go to compare the dates to the detail lines on the claim later on."
